    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The documentation states (http://cython.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/tutorial/strings.html#passing-byte-strings) that to cast a python bytes/bytearray-object one has simple to use:\r\n\r\n`cdef char* other_c_string = py_string`\r\n\r\nWhat is not directly obvious, whether this resulting C-string is null-terminated.\r\n\r\nPlease consider to clarify in documentation, that the resulting C-string is `\\0` terminated.\r\n\r\nPython-3 documenation states it explicitly here https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/bytes.html#c.PyBytes_AsString and here https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/bytearray.html#c.PyByteArray_AsString \r\n\r\nPython-2 documentation lacks this assurance, but judging from the code e.g. https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/2.7/Objects/bytearrayobject.c#L288 this is also the case.",
